data.title: The Greatest Penguin Characters of All Time
data.meta_description: Over 1K fans have voted on the 30+ characters on Greatest Penguin Characters of All Time. Current Top 3: Private, Pingu, Rico
data.text:
Ranked By

7.4K votes

1.2K voters

Voting Rules

Vote up your favorite fictional penguin characters.

For this poll we've created a list of the greatest penguins of all time, featuring penguins you know from movies, television, video games and more. Of course your favorite cartoon penguins are included, but this list doesn't only feature animated characters that can talk. If your favorite fictional penguin is missing, don't be salty- just add it to the list so that other people can vote for for it too!Examples include Opus the Penguin and Chilly Willy. Who is the number one penguin that people just can't get enough of? Scroll down and find out who the masses voted for.

Adored for his innocence and naive nature, Private has captured audiences' hearts as a kind-hearted member of the Madagascar penguin family. Despite being considered the runt of his group, he possesses an unyielding desire to prove himself and protect his comrades. Private's unassuming charm shines through, whether he's diffusing tensions or stumbling upon brilliant solutions in the nick of time. Audiences cannot help but fall in love with this adorable underdog with a heart of gold.

Appears In : Madagascar

Also ranks # 54 on 'Nickelodeon All-Star Brawl' DLC Characters We Want The Most

Also ranks # 11 on The Best Bird Characters From Cartoons & Comics

As the mischievous star of a beloved claymation series, Pingu captured the imagination of audiences through his expressive and heartwarming adventures. Overcoming language barriers with his quirky "penguinese," he navigates life in the Antarctic with curiosity and playfulness. Despite his troublemaking tendencies, Pingu consistently learns essential life lessons and demonstrates a genuine love for his family and friends. His unique charm and relatability have cemented Pingu as a timeless icon in children's entertainment.

Appears In : Pingu

Rico, the wild card of the Madagascar penguins, provides explosive humor (quite literally) as the demolitions expert. With a penchant for swallowing and regurgitating an arsenal of weapons, he packs quite a punch and always keeps audiences on their toes. His unpredictable actions and insatiable appetite for destruction make him an unforgettable character, embodying chaos in every waddle. Rico's offbeat, yet lovable nature adds a delightful dose of excitement to every scene he's in.

Appears In : Madagascar

Also ranks # 38 on 'Nickelodeon All-Star Brawl' DLC Characters We Want The Most

Also ranks # 12 on The Best Bird Characters From Cartoons & Comics

Always equipped with a trusty clipboard in his flippers, Kowalski stands out as the brains of the penguin squad in Madagascar. Known for his analytical mind and dry sense of humor, he conducts experiments and invents ingenious devices to aid their daring escapades. This highly intelligent penguin consistently delivers both entertainment and inspiration with his resourcefulness and quick thinking. Kowalski is a quintessential example of a lovable geek, proving that even in the animal kingdom, knowledge is power.

Appears In : Madagascar

Also ranks # 66 on 'Nickelodeon All-Star Brawl' DLC Characters We Want The Most

Also ranks # 13 on The Best Bird Characters From Cartoons & Comics

Hidden beneath a layer of squeaky cuteness lies the wisdom of Wheezy from Toy Story 2. Overcoming adversity in the form of a broken squeaker, he serves as a testament to resilience and perseverance. As an unassuming source of comic relief and inspiration, Wheezy swiftly wins audiences over with his sweet disposition and undeniable charm. Ultimately, his narrative underscores the importance of acknowledging one's worth, even amid tribulations.

Appears In : Toy Story films

Navigating the realm of Madagascar with courage and wit, Skipper leads his squad of quirky penguins through countless adventures. As the daring and resourceful head honcho of the group, he exudes charisma and an uncanny ability to strategize. Never one to back down from a challenge, Skipper's resilience and loyalty cement him as an iconic and loveable penguin hero. Whether it is one of his cunning plans or his memorable catchphrases, Skipper's appeal transcends age groups, making him a timeless fan favorite.

Appears In : Madagascar
